CV by hand

data for a non-linear model

nonlin_df = 
  tibble(
    id = 1:100,
    x = runif(100, 0, 1),
    y = 1 - 10 * (x - .3) ^ 2 + rnorm(100, 0, .3)
  )

nonlin_df %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = x, y = y)) + 
  geom_point()

splitting data into training and test data sets

train_df = sample_n(nonlin_df, 80)
test_df = anti_join(nonlin_df, train_df, by = "id")

ggplot(train_df, aes(x = x, y = y)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  geom_point(data = test_df, color = "red")

creating 3 different models

linear_mod = lm(y ~ x, data = train_df)
smooth_mod = mgcv::gam(y ~ s(x), data = train_df)
wiggly_mod = mgcv::gam(y ~ s(x, k = 30), sp = 10e-6, data = train_df)

plotting 2 of the models

train_df %>% 
  add_predictions(smooth_mod) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = x, y = y)) + geom_point() + geom_point(data = test_df, color = "blue") +
  geom_line(aes(y = pred), color = "red")

train_df %>% 
  add_predictions(wiggly_mod) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = x, y = y)) + geom_point() + geom_point(data = test_df, color = "blue") + 
  geom_line(aes(y = pred), color = "red")

train_df %>% 
  gather_predictions(linear_mod, smooth_mod, wiggly_mod) %>% 
  mutate(model = fct_inorder(model)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = x, y = y)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  geom_line(aes(y = pred), color = "red") + 
  facet_wrap(~model)

root mean squared errors (RMSEs) for each model

rmse(linear_mod, test_df)
## [1] 0.7052956
rmse(smooth_mod, test_df)
## [1] 0.2221774
rmse(wiggly_mod, test_df)
## [1] 0.289051

CV using modelr

cv_df =
  crossv_mc(nonlin_df, 100) %>% 
  mutate(
    train = map(train, as_tibble),
    test = map(test, as_tibble))

fit models and obtain RMSEs using mutate + map & map2

cv_df = 
  cv_df %>% 
  mutate(
    linear_mod  = map(.x = train, ~lm(y ~ x, data = .x)),
    smooth_mod  = map(.x = train, ~mgcv::gam(y ~ s(x), data = .x)),
    wiggly_mod  = map(.x = train, ~gam(y ~ s(x, k = 30), sp = 10e-6, data = .x))) %>% 
  mutate(
    rmse_linear = map2_dbl(linear_mod, test, ~rmse(model = .x, data = .y)),
    rmse_smooth = map2_dbl(smooth_mod, test, ~rmse(model = .x, data = .y)),
    rmse_wiggly = map2_dbl(wiggly_mod, test, ~rmse(model = .x, data = .y)))

plotting RMSEs

cv_df %>% 
  select(starts_with("rmse")) %>% 
  pivot_longer(
    everything(),
    names_to = "model", 
    values_to = "rmse",
    names_prefix = "rmse_") %>% 
  mutate(model = fct_inorder(model)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = model, y = rmse)) + geom_violin()

Case Study:

child_growth = read_csv("./nepalese_children.csv")
## Rows: 2705 Columns: 5
## ── Column specification ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## Delimiter: ","
## dbl (5): age, sex, weight, height, armc
## 
## ℹ Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
## ℹ Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
child_growth %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = weight, y = armc)) + 
  geom_point(alpha = .5)

child_growth =
  child_growth %>% 
  mutate(weight_cp = (weight > 7) * (weight - 7))


linear_mod = lm(armc ~ weight, data = child_growth)
pwl_mod    = lm(armc ~ weight + weight_cp, data = child_growth)
smooth_mod = gam(armc ~ s(weight), data = child_growth)
child_growth %>% 
  gather_predictions(linear_mod, pwl_mod, smooth_mod) %>% 
  mutate(model = fct_inorder(model)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = weight, y = armc)) + 
  geom_point(alpha = .5) +
  geom_line(aes(y = pred), color = "red") + 
  facet_grid(~model)

given 1 dataset, generate 100 different train/test splits

cv_df =
  crossv_mc(child_growth, 100) %>% 
  mutate(
    train = map(train, as_tibble),
    test = map(test, as_tibble))
cv_df = 
  cv_df %>% 
  mutate(
    linear_mod  = map(train, ~lm(armc ~ weight, data = .x)),
    pwl_mod     = map(train, ~lm(armc ~ weight + weight_cp, data = .x)),
    smooth_mod  = map(train, ~gam(armc ~ s(weight), data = as_tibble(.x)))) %>% 
  mutate(
    rmse_linear = map2_dbl(linear_mod, test, ~rmse(model = .x, data = .y)),
    rmse_pwl    = map2_dbl(pwl_mod, test, ~rmse(model = .x, data = .y)),
    rmse_smooth = map2_dbl(smooth_mod, test, ~rmse(model = .x, data = .y)))
cv_df %>% 
  select(starts_with("rmse")) %>% 
  pivot_longer(
    everything(),
    names_to = "model", 
    values_to = "rmse",
    names_prefix = "rmse_") %>% 
  mutate(model = fct_inorder(model)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = model, y = rmse)) + geom_violin()
